FT  13 JUN 92 / UK Company News: Morland in deal with Courage
Morland, the Oxfordshire-based brewer facing a hostile bid from Greene King,
has announced a brewing and marketing tie-up with Courage which it claimed
could earn it Pounds 800,000 a year in profits,
Morland will sell Courage at least 5,000 barrels each year of Old Speckled
Hen, its premium cask beer. Morland will also brew 20,000 barrels per year
of Courage beers and make its products more available.
The agreement, which is planned to last five years, is subject to Greene
King's bid lapsing or being withdrawn.
